&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; This club deeply believes in advocating for the respect of all animals, regardless of their species. We demonstrate this belief by building a strong student-led community and leading student initiatives to take action against the institutions that perpetuate the inhumane and disrespectful treatment of animals. We aim to help students identify the best ways of helping animals through education and facilitation of professional connections. We aim to create a strong student community where individuals interested in the well-being of animals can come together regardless of their dietary choices or beliefs.&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; We will work towards the equal treatment of species by focusing on the institutions that perpetuate the continued oppression of non-human animals. We will pressure dining halls to implement more plant-based options, enable students to pursue impactful careers in animal advocacy, and give students experience in pressuring politicians to reform biased legislatures.&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; This organization will also focus its energy towards building the community around us into something capable of taking larger, meaningful action. We will facilitate student&rsquo;s' personal projects and career paths that align with our purpose, and lead student volunteer outreach to local animal sanctuaries. Additionally, we will provide further education around the ethical discussion of our society&rsquo;s relationship with non-human animals to any interested individuals. This Animal Ethics Fellowship will be guided by our facilitators through a structured curriculum over 5 weeks in small group discussions. This course will cover topics such as moral expansion, veganism, the intersectionality of animal advocacy and social justice movements, as well as topics requested by students.
