The Badger Caring Closet is a no-cost personal essentials and clothing pantry. We work
with The Keep Food Pantry to help mitigate the effect of housing instability on campus so
that students can focus their energies on their academic and career pursuits. Each week, we serve around 150+ students, staff, and faculty from UW Madison, Madison College, and
Edgewood College.&nbsp;
Open on Thursdays during the school year from 2:30-5:30pm out of the basement of Luther Memorial Church. Our mission is to&nbsp;promote student well-being by serving all students with no-cost non-food essentials and clothing. The BCC is managed, stocked, and run by students throughout the year with the help of clothing, product, and monetary drives and donations.&nbsp;
If you have questions or are interested in joining the Badger Caring Closet, please reach out at badgercaringclosetuw@gmail.com or follow us on instagram at badgercaringclosetuw!

Badger Consulting is a student-run consulting group at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. Students are offered an unparalleled experience to work with small businesses in various market sectors while obtaining real-world knowledge in the consulting industry.&nbsp;
Badger Consulting provides pro-bono consulting in the fields of industry research, consumer insights, marketing analytics, and financial viabilities. Badger Consulting is grateful to be supervised and mentored by the Wisconsin Small Business Development Center (WI SBDC). The WI SBDC at UW-Madison provides no cost consulting and non-credit courses to help businesses from start-up through growth.&nbsp;
Badger Consulting is proud of its professional relationships and inclusive environment that fosters lifelong friendships and contributes to its robust alumni network.

Product managers sit at the intersection of tech, design, and business. They talk to users, analyze data, and work with designers and engineers to turn ideas into real, impactful products. PMs are decision-makers, communicators, and the voice of the customer &mdash; all rolled into one.&nbsp;
The Product Management Club at UW&ndash;Madison exists to help students break into this high-impact career path &mdash; through real skill-building, mentorship, and hands-on product experiences.&nbsp;
We offer:
&nbsp;
Educational Sessions: Learn the PM fundamentals &mdash; product thinking, user research, wireframing, roadmapping, and more.
Mentorship: Get guidance from students and professionals with experience in product, tech, and consulting.
Product Challenges: Tackle real-world prompts in team settings that simulate the PM interview and feature design process.
Career Exploration: Understand how PM connects to other fields like engineering, UX, data, software, and business strategy.
&nbsp;
Whether you're a CS major, an aspiring engineer, a business student, a designer, or just someone who likes building things &mdash; this is where you can explore what it means to own a product.

