SB&sup2; strives to be a catalyst for social change, through innovative ideas and entrepreneurial strategies. The goal is to implement social change that self-sustain and work to solve issues at their roots, bettering the communities around them.
Vision:&nbsp;&nbsp;
To form a group of like minded, passionate, and self motivated students, who meet and implement social innovations in the Madison and UW community. This is accomplished through meetings 1-2 times per month that plan, collaborate, and host events. More so, SB&sup2; collaborates with other student organizations and the surrounding community to discuss social entrepreneurship, raise funds, and demonstrate concepts related to social entrepreneurship, social innovation, and social business. Additionally, SB&sup2; invites guest speakers to bolster learning outside of the classroom and focus around career application.
