Monday &ndash; Zoom drop-in session, 6:00-6:30pm
Wednesday &ndash; In-person Anytime, Anywhere Meditation program, 6:00-7:15pm, 6 sessions
Thursday- In-person drop-in session, 6:00-6:30pm
&nbsp;
To obtain the Zoom link and schedule details, please email our President: Zoe Nickchen, znickchen@wisc.edu

TNEPS is committed to providing a forum for law students interested in trusts and estate planning to engage in an educational dialogue about the needs of both individual members of the community as well as industry broadly for trusts and estate planning skills. In pursuit of that commitment, the purposes of the TNEPS are to:&nbsp;
(1)Articulate the importance of trusts and estate planning within the University of Wisconsin Law School community;
(2)Facilitate the creation of relationships between law students, attorneys practicing elder law, and professional organizations which focus on elder law and estate planning;
(3)Encourage students, legal fraternities, and associations to use their expertise and prestige to make the legal community more responsive to the estate planning needs of the broader community.

UNIT.E is a dance team that celebrates styles of dance throughout the world and recognizes its cultural significance. This team is comprised of talented individuals who teach diverse styles of dance to better ourselves in dance technicality, endurance, and confidence. Dance styles that we participate in include but are not limited to, Hip-hop, K-pop, Bollywood, Reggaeton, Lyrical, and Freestyling. We conduct a semester mix of member-led original choreographies as well as an inclusive curation of choreographies.&nbsp;&nbsp;
We welcome people of all dance backgrounds and skill levels as we value teaching and enhancing your technical dance skills. We are a loving and supportive community that will always hype you up to reach YOUR best potential!
UNIT.E was founded by a Brooklyn native, Ebonie Reavis, who is trained in dance for over a decade ranging from Russian Ballet, Lyrical, K-pop, and Hip-hop, with a dream to create and build an uplifting community for all dancers to truly be the most creative and expressive.&nbsp;

